00:32:29.510 --> 00:32:33.980
and I'm going to talk a little bit
about my own subcultural space.

00:32:33.980 --> 00:32:38.060
My group positioned
itself on the frontier,

00:32:38.060 --> 00:32:41.840
the border between superculture
and subculture very deliberately.

00:32:41.840 --> 00:32:45.000
The Jews turned inward
musically in their own practices,

00:32:45.000 --> 00:32:46.400
and I'll talk about that.

00:32:46.400 --> 00:32:49.770
But they also pushed resolutely
outward into the mainstream

00:32:49.770 --> 00:32:53.120
as a part of a generalized policy.

00:32:53.120 --> 00:32:56.860
The Jews encapsulate the anxieties
and achievements in minority agency

00:32:56.860 --> 00:32:59.230
in ways that differ from
these other activities

00:32:59.230 --> 00:33:01.590
of all these other groups
I've been mentioning.

00:33:01.590 --> 00:33:06.310
The community mushroomed in the
1910s, jumping in a few years

00:33:06.310 --> 00:33:09.730
from 10,000 to 50,000, including
my grandfather and great-uncles,

00:33:09.730 --> 00:33:11.440
and peaked at around 90,000.

00:33:11.440 --> 00:33:15.020
So it was a pretty large
minority within Detroit.

00:33:15.020 --> 00:33:16.660
They were all in a
single neighborhood,

00:33:16.660 --> 00:33:20.190
and they were deeply divided
on all kinds of lines.

00:33:20.190 --> 00:33:24.000
One scholar says, "Different voices
seem to cry out in disharmony

00:33:24.000 --> 00:33:27.400
for resolutions to a confusing
mixture of problems and questions,"

00:33:27.400 --> 00:33:28.980
about the Jewish community.

00:33:28.980 --> 00:33:31.210
And I think anybody who
knows a Jewish community,

00:33:31.210 --> 00:33:32.510
this pretty much right.

00:33:32.510 --> 00:33:35.110
So I can talk about
two little trends.

00:33:35.110 --> 00:33:38.050
One is the extroverted
tendency to push outward

00:33:38.050 --> 00:33:41.080
in classical music
cosmopolitanism and the kind

00:33:41.080 --> 00:33:44.590
of interior religious practice.

00:33:44.590 --> 00:33:47.470
The newly-emancipated
Jews of Europe,

00:33:47.470 --> 00:33:51.230
starting around 1800 used
European classical music as a way

00:33:51.230 --> 00:33:55.340
to join the mainstream in ways that
are strategic but also deeply-felt.

00:33:55.340 --> 00:33:57.460 position:56%
You think of Mendelssohn and Mahler.

00:33:57.460 --> 00:33:59.860
But also all the orchestra
members and the audience

00:33:59.860 --> 00:34:03.920
that supported classical music
in Berlin, and Vienna, Odessa,

00:34:03.920 --> 00:34:05.450
Kiev, Warsaw, every city.

00:34:05.450 --> 00:34:07.910
And there is no book on
this, which is amazing.

00:34:07.910 --> 00:34:09.230
There's no book about that.

00:34:09.230 --> 00:34:13.750
I started violin lessons
at the age of four, right.

00:34:13.750 --> 00:34:15.470
&gt;&gt; Aww!

00:34:15.470 --> 00:34:18.340
